The widow of the late zakawanu Garuba has been kidnapped by unknown gunmen, LEADERSHIP has learnt. Hassana Garuba, her three children and a the aged mother of the late Former Speaker were on their way home from Abuja to prepare for the burial of their bread winner when unknown gunmen abducted the widow and the driver at kabba junction in Kogi State, leaving the three children and their grand mother stranded in the vehicle. A younger brother of the late zakawanu Garuba said the kidnappers are yet to establish contact with the family but arrangements have been made to bring the children and their grand mother home.